    "ID": "W10-4128",
    "sections": [
        {
            "text": "abstract",
            "number": 0,
            "sents": [
                {
                    "text": "This paper presents a Chinese word segmentation system for CIPSSIGHAN 2010 Chinese language processing task.",
                    "sid": 1,
                    "ssid": 1,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "Firstly, based on Conditional Random Field (CRF) model, with local features and global features, the character-based tagging model is designed.",
                    "sid": 2,
                    "ssid": 2,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "Secondly, Hidden Markov Models (HMM) is used to revise the substrings with low marginal probability by CRF.",
                    "sid": 3,
                    "ssid": 3,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "Finally, confidence measure is used to regenerate the result and simple rules to deal with the strings within letters and numbers.",
                    "sid": 4,
                    "ssid": 4,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "As is well known that character-based approach has outstanding capability of discovering out-of-vocabulary (OOV) word, but external information of word lost.",
                    "sid": 5,
                    "ssid": 5,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "HMM makes use of word information to increase in-vocabulary (IV) recall.",
                    "sid": 6,
                    "ssid": 6,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "We participate in the simplified Chinese word segmentation both closed and open test on all four corpora, which belong to different domains.",
                    "sid": 7,
                    "ssid": 7,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "Our system achieves better performance.",
                    "sid": 8,
                    "ssid": 8,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "introduction",
            "number": "1",
            "sents": [
                {
                    "text": "Chinese Word Segmentation (CWS) has witnessed a prominent progress in the first four SIGHAN Bakeoffs.",
                    "sid": 9,
                    "ssid": 9,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "Since Xue (2003) used character-based tagging, this method has attracted more and more attention.",
                    "sid": 10,
                    "ssid": 10,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "Some previous work (Peng et al., 2004; Tseng et al., 2005; Low et al., 2005) illustrated the effectiveness of using characters as tagging units, while literatures (Zhang et al., 2006; Zhao and Kit, 2007a; Zhang and Clark, 2007) focus on employing lexical words or subwords as tagging units.",
                    "sid": 11,
                    "ssid": 11,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "Because the word-based models can capture the word-level contextual information and IV knowledge.",
                    "sid": 12,
                    "ssid": 12,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "Besides, many strategies are proposed to balance the IV and OOV performance (Wang et al., 2008).",
                    "sid": 13,
                    "ssid": 13,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "CRF has been widely used in sequence labeling tasks and has a good performance (Laffertyet al., 2001).",
                    "sid": 14,
                    "ssid": 14,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "Zhao and Kit (2007b; 2008) at tempt to integrate global information with local information to further improve CRF-based tagging method of CWS, which provides a solid foundation for strengthening CRF learning with unsupervised learning outcomes.",
                    "sid": 15,
                    "ssid": 15,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "In order to increase the accuracy of tagging using CRF, we adopt the strategy, which is: if the marginal probability of characters is lower than a threshold, the modified component based on HMM will be trigged; combining the confidence measure the results will be regenerated.",
                    "sid": 16,
                    "ssid": 16,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "our word segmentation system. ",
            "number": "2",
            "sents": [
                {
                    "text": "In this section, we describe our system in more details.",
                    "sid": 17,
                    "ssid": 1,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "Three modules are included in our system: a basic character-based CRF tagger, HMM which revises the substrings with low marginal probability and confidence measure which combines them to regenerate the result.",
                    "sid": 18,
                    "ssid": 2,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "In addition, we also use some rules to deal with the strings within letters and numbers.",
                    "sid": 19,
                    "ssid": 3,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "2.1 Character-based CRF tagger.",
                    "sid": 20,
                    "ssid": 4,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "Tag Set A 6-tag set is adopted in our system.",
                    "sid": 21,
                    "ssid": 5,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "It includes six tags: B, B2, B3, M, E and S. Here, Tag B and E stand for the first and the last position in a multi-character word, respectively.",
                    "sid": 22,
                    "ssid": 6,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "S stands for a single-character word.",
                    "sid": 23,
                    "ssid": 7,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "B2 and B3 stand for the second and the third position in a The work described in this paper is supported by Microsoft Research Asia Funded Project.",
                    "sid": 24,
                    "ssid": 8,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "multi-character word.",
                    "sid": 25,
                    "ssid": 9,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "M stands for the fourth or more rear position in a multi-character word with more than four characters.",
                    "sid": 26,
                    "ssid": 10,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "The 6-tag set is proved to work more effectively than other tag sets in improving the segmentation performance of CRFs by Zhao et al.",
                    "sid": 27,
                    "ssid": 11,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "(2006).",
                    "sid": 28,
                    "ssid": 12,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "Feature templates In our system, six n-gram templates, namely, C-1, C0, C1, C-1C0, C0C1, that character.",
                    "sid": 29,
                    "ssid": 13,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "In the open test, we only add another feature of \u2018FRE\u2019, the basic idea of which is if a string matches a word in an existing dictionary, it may be a clue that the string is likely a true word.",
                    "sid": 30,
                    "ssid": 14,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "Then more word boundary information can be obtained, which may be helpful for CRF learning on CWS.",
                    "sid": 31,
                    "ssid": 15,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "The dictionary we used is \u2460 C-1C1 are selected as features, where C stands for downloaded from the Internet and consists of a character and the subscripts -1, 0 and 1 stand for the previous, current and next character, respectively.",
                    "sid": 32,
                    "ssid": 16,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "Furthermore, another one is character type feature template T-1T0T1.",
                    "sid": 33,
                    "ssid": 17,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "We use four classes of character sets which are predefined as: class N represents numbers, class L represents non-Chinese letters, class P represents punctuation labels and class C represents Chinese characters.",
                    "sid": 34,
                    "ssid": 18,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "Except for the character feature, we also employ global word feature templates.",
                    "sid": 35,
                    "ssid": 19,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "The basic idea of using global word information for CWS is to inform the supervised learner how likely it is that the subsequence can be a word candidate.108,750 words with length of one to four char acters.",
                    "sid": 36,
                    "ssid": 20,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "We get FRE features similar to the AV features.",
                    "sid": 37,
                    "ssid": 21,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "2.2 HMM revises substrings with low mar-.",
                    "sid": 38,
                    "ssid": 22,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "ginal probability The MP (short for marginal probability) of each character labeled with one of the six tags can be got separately through the basic CRF tagger.",
                    "sid": 39,
                    "ssid": 23,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "Here, B replaces \u2018B\u2019 and \u2018S\u2019 , and I represents other tags (\u2018B2\u2019, \u2018B3\u2019, \u2018M\u2019, \u2018E\u2019).",
                    "sid": 40,
                    "ssid": 24,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "So each character has corresponding new MP as defined in formula (3) and (4).",
                    "sid": 41,
                    "ssid": 25,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "The accessor variety (AV) (Feng et al., 2005) is opted as global word feature, which is integrated into CRF successfully in literatures (Zhao and Kit, 2007b; Zhao and Kit, 2008).",
                    "sid": 42,
                    "ssid": 26,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "The AV value P ( PS B \u2211 PB ) Pt (3) of a substring s is defined as: ( P P PM P 2 3 PE ) (4) AV (s) min Lav (s), Rav (s) (1) I Where \u2211 Pt t S, B, B2 , B3 , M, E and Pt can be Where the left and right AV values Lav (s) calculated by using forward-backward algorithm and more details are in Lafferty et al.",
                    "sid": 43,
                    "ssid": 27,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "(2001).",
                    "sid": 44,
                    "ssid": 28,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "and Rav (s) are defin ed, respe ctivel y, as the A low confi dent word refer s to a word with number of its distinct predecessors and the number of its distinct successors.",
                    "sid": 45,
                    "ssid": 29,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "Multiple feature templates are used to represent word candidates of various lengths identified by the AV criterion.",
                    "sid": 46,
                    "ssid": 30,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "Meanwhile, in order to alleviate the sparse data problem, we follow the feature function definition for a word candidate word boundary ambiguity which can be reflected by the MP of the first character of a word.",
                    "sid": 47,
                    "ssid": 31,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "That is, it\u2019s a low confident word if the MP of the first character of the word is lower than a threshold (it\u2019s an empirical value and can be obtained by experiments).",
                    "sid": 48,
                    "ssid": 32,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "After getting the new MP, all s with a score AV (s) namely: in Zhao and Kit (2008), these low confident candidate words are recom bined with their direct predecessors until the occurrence of a word that the MP of its first fn (s) t , 2 t AV (s) 2t 1 (2) character is above the threshold , and then a In order to improve the efficiency, all candidates longer than five characters are given up.",
                    "sid": 49,
                    "ssid": 33,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "The AV features of word candidates can\u2019t directly be utilized to direct CRF learning before being transferred to the information of characters.",
                    "sid": 50,
                    "ssid": 34,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "So we only choose the one with the greatest AV score to activate the above feature function for new substring is generated for post processing.",
                    "sid": 51,
                    "ssid": 35,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "Then, we use class-based HMM to re-segment the substrings mentioned above.",
                    "sid": 52,
                    "ssid": 36,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "Given a word \u2460http://ccl.pku.edu.cn/doubtfire/Course/Chinese%20Inform ation%20Processing/Source_Code/Chapter_8/Lexicon_full.",
                    "sid": 53,
                    "ssid": 37,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
