        {
            "text": "conclusions and future work. ",
            "number": "4",
            "sents": [
                {
                    "text": "In this paper, a detailed description on a Chinese segmentation system is presented.",
                    "sid": 182,
                    "ssid": 1,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "Based on intermediate results from a CRF tagger, which employs local features and global features, we use class-based HMM to revise the substrings with low marginal probabilities.",
                    "sid": 183,
                    "ssid": 2,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "Then, a confidence measure is introduced to combine the two results.",
                    "sid": 184,
                    "ssid": 3,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "Finally, we post process the strings within letters, numbers and punctuations using simple rules.",
                    "sid": 185,
                    "ssid": 4,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "The results above show that our system achieves the state-of-the-art performance.",
                    "sid": 186,
                    "ssid": 5,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "The MP plays the important role in our method and HMM revises some errors identified by CRF.",
                    "sid": 187,
                    "ssid": 6,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "Besides, the word features are proved to be informative cues in obtaining high quality MP.",
                    "sid": 188,
                    "ssid": 7,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                },
                {
                    "text": "Therefore, our future work will focus on how to make CRF generate more reliable MP of characters, including exploring other word information or more unsupervised segmentation information.",
                    "sid": 189,
                    "ssid": 8,
                    "kind_of_tag": "s"
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
